      <tr>
        <td id="L379" class="blob-num js-line-number" data-line-number="379"></td>
        <td id="LC379" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">	<span class="pl-s">Abstract</span> = <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">{</span>We propose an approach that predicts whether a tweet, which is accompanied by multimedia content (image/video), is trustworthy or deceptive. We test different combinations of quality and trust-oriented features (tweet-based, user- based and forensics) in tandem with a standard classification and an agreement-retraining technique, with the goal of pre- dicting the most likely label (fake or real) for each tweet. The experiments carried out on the Verifying Multimedia Use dataset show that the best performance is achieved when using all available features in combination with the agreement-retraining method.<span class="pl-pds">}</span></span>,</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td id="L380" class="blob-num js-line-number" data-line-number="380"></td>
